title.narrative: Open Innovation Booster and Lead Optimization consortium

description.narrative: 1. Open Synthesis Network : a collaborative project that aims to engage master’s and undergraduate students in research for neglected diseases. 2. The NTD Drug Discovery Booster: a project that aims to speed up the process and cut the cost of finding new treatments for leishmaniasis and Chagas disease. It brings together DNDi and seven pharmaceutical companies. 3. MycetOS: an open source approach to discover compounds that could lead to new treatments for fungal mycetoma. The project uses open-access data and collaborative methods in a virtual research community.

Open innovation at DNDi continues to grow and expand ranging from work with university chemistry teaching labs to support drug discovery through to a virtual Open Pharma community to support lead optimization of chemical compounds that could one day become new medicines. The finality of these projects is to speed up the process cut the cost of finding new treatments and/or evaluate alternative research mechanisms by bringing together collaborators from across all sectors in a multilateral simultaneous and non-competitive R&D process.
